# API Specifications Index
**Integration Architecture - OpenAPI Specifications**  
**Last Updated**: 2026-04-10

---

## Overview

This directory contains OpenAPI 3.1.0 specifications for all microservices and main API endpoints in the Sovereign Governance Substrate. All specifications include implementation status and links to actual code.

---

## Specifications

### Main API (Port 8000)

| Specification | Description | Implementation | Status |
|--------------|-------------|----------------|--------|
| **explainability-api.yaml** | AI decision explainability | api/main.py | ✅ Complete |
| **save-points-api.yaml** | Time-travel debugging & recovery | api/save_points_routes.py | ✅ Complete |
| **vr-routes-api.yaml** | VR command routing | api/vr_routes.py | ✅ Complete |

### Core Microservices

| Service | Specification | Port | Implementation | Status |
|---------|--------------|------|----------------|--------|
| **Sovereign Data Vault** | `sovereign-data-vault-api.yaml` | 8012 | emergent-microservices/sovereign-data-vault | 🔄 Generic CRUD |
| **Trust Graph Engine** | `trust-graph-engine-api.yaml` | 8013 | emergent-microservices/trust-graph-engine | 🔄 Generic CRUD |
| **Autonomous Compliance** | `autonomous-compliance-api.yaml` | 8014 | emergent-microservices/autonomous-compliance | 🔄 Generic CRUD |
| **Autonomous Incident Reflex** | `autonomous-incident-reflex-system-api.yaml` | 8015 | emergent-microservices/autonomous-incident-reflex-system | 🔄 Basic + Planned |
| **Autonomous Negotiation Agent** | `autonomous-negotiation-agent-api.yaml` | 8016 | emergent-microservices/autonomous-negotiation-agent | 🔄 Generic CRUD |
| **Verifiable Reality** | `verifiable-reality-api.yaml` | 8017 | emergent-microservices/verifiable-reality | 🔄 Generic CRUD |

**Status Legend**:
- ✅ Complete: Fully implemented as spec
- 🔄 Generic CRUD: Using `/api/v1/items` pattern (spec-defined endpoints planned)
- 🔄 Basic + Planned: Core features implemented, advanced features planned

### Archived Specifications

See `archive/` directory for deprecated or superseded specifications.

---

## Common Endpoints (All Services)

### Health Checks
```
GET /api/v1/health/liveness   - Kubernetes liveness probe
GET /api/v1/health/readiness  - Kubernetes readiness probe
GET /api/v1/health/startup    - Kubernetes startup probe
```

### Observability
```
GET /metrics                   - Prometheus metrics (text/plain)
```

### Documentation
```
GET /api/v1/docs              - Swagger UI
GET /api/v1/redoc             - ReDoc documentation
GET /api/v1/openapi.json      - OpenAPI specification
```

---

## Authentication

All APIs support dual authentication:

### API Key Authentication
```http
GET /api/v1/resource
X-API-Key: your-api-key-here
```

### JWT Bearer Token
```http
GET /api/v1/resource
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...
```

---

## Usage

### Viewing Specifications

**Swagger UI** (Interactive):
```bash
# Local
http://localhost:8011/api/v1/docs

# Docker network
http://mutation-firewall:8000/api/v1/docs
```

**ReDoc** (Documentation):
```bash
http://localhost:8011/api/v1/redoc
```

### Generating Client Libraries

#### Python
```bash
openapi-generator-cli generate \
  -i API_SPECIFICATIONS/mutation-firewall-api.json \
  -g python \
  -o clients/python/mutation-firewall
```

#### TypeScript
```bash
openapi-generator-cli generate \
  -i API_SPECIFICATIONS/trust-graph-api.json \
  -g typescript-axios \
  -o clients/typescript/trust-graph
```

---

## Rate Limiting

Default rate limits:
- **Authenticated**: 1000 requests/hour, burst of 100
- **Unauthenticated**: 100 requests/hour, burst of 10

## Testing APIs

```bash
# Using newman (Postman CLI)
newman run postman_collection.json -e environment.json

# Validate OpenAPI specs
swagger-cli validate API_SPECIFICATIONS/*.yaml
```

## Service Mesh Integration

All APIs configured for Istio service mesh with mTLS STRICT mode. See `k8s/istio/` for configurations.

